:"Stapleford","village":"Stapleford","town":"Salisbury","county":"Wiltshire","postcode":"SP2","hubCity":"Salisbury","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Salisbury","coords":{"lat":51.05432,"lng":-1.82112},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"steep-gu32","name":"Steep","village":"Steep","town":"Petersfield","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"GU32","hubCity":"Guildford","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Petersfield","coords":{"lat":51.00216,"lng":-0.93096},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"A village and civil parish in the East Hampshire district, about 1.4 miles north of Petersfield and just inside the western edge of the South Downs National Park, at the foot of the wooded slopes of Stoner Hill and Wheatham Hill. Steep is notable for two things. First, Bedales School (founded 1893 in Lindfield, moved here in 1900) — a co-educational boarding and day independent school with a progressive ethos, which from the early 20th century drew a community of artists, craftsmen and writers to the village: Edward Thomas the war poet lived here from 1906 to 1916, and Alec Guinness, Stanley Spencer, Ernest Gimson and Edward Barnsley all had connections. Second, The Harrow Inn — a 17th-century Grade II listed pub on CAMRA''s National Inventory of Historic Pub Interiors, run by the same family since 1932 and serving cask beer drawn straight from the barrel. Population at the 2011 census was 1,391 (civil parish). The Church of All Saints dates from around 1125.","character":"Genuinely literary, slightly bohemian downland village with deep Arts and Crafts roots; mix of period cottages, larger Arts-and-Crafts and Edwardian houses (some by W. F. Unsworth), Bedales-influenced modernist commissions, and 20th-century infill. Strong cultural fabric — Edward Thomas associations, Bedales archive, Edward Barnsley Workshop, village film society founded by Alec Guinness''s legacy.","amenities":["Bedales School (independent, 3–18, ~760 pupils)","Steep CofE Voluntary Controlled Primary School","The Harrow Inn (Grade II listed, CAMRA National Inventory)","The Cricketers Inn","All Saints Church (12th century, Grade II* listed)","Edward Barnsley Workshop (Arts and Crafts furniture)","Steep Village Hall (film society, talks)","Eight-court floodlit tennis club and adjoining cricket ground","Poet''s Stone (Edward Thomas memorial) on Shoulder of Mutton Hill"],"schools":[{"name":"Steep Church of England Voluntary Controlled Primary School","phase":"Primary","ofsted":"Good quality of education; Outstanding behaviour and early years (Oct 2024 inspection, no overall grade under new framework)","distance":"in village","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/116319"},{"name":"Bedales School","phase":"Independent (3–18, boarding and day)","ofsted":null,"distance":"in village","url":"https://www.bedales.org.uk/"},{"name":"The Petersfield School","phase":"Secondary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"2.5 mi","url":"https://www.tps.hants.sch.uk/"},{"name":"Churcher''s College","phase":"Independent (3–18)","ofsted":null,"distance":"1.7 mi","url":"https://www.churcherscollege.com/"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"London Waterloo","time":"1h 2m – 1h 17m direct","mode":"walk/cycle/drive to Petersfield + direct South Western Railway","source":"https://www.southwesternrailway.com/train-times/petersfield-to-london-waterloo"},{"to":"Portsmouth Harbour","time":"~30m","mode":"Petersfield + direct South Western Railway","source":"https://www.southwesternrailway.com/travelling-with-us/at-the-station/petersfield"}],"nearestStation":"Petersfield (1.6 mi)","roads":"A3 (London–Portsmouth) ~2 mi east at Petersfield; A272 (Winchester–Midhurst) at south of the parish"},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":null,"avgDetached":null,"avgSemi":null,"avgTerraced":null,"avgFlat":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/gu32.html","asOf":"2026-05"},"thingsToDo":["Hangers Way walk to Shoulder of Mutton Hill and the Poet''s Stone","Edward Thomas literary trail (Berryfield Cottage, The Red House, Yew Tree Cottages)","Edward Barnsley Workshop tours","Steep village film society and talks","Bedales Arts (public concerts and theatre productions)","Cycling on Sustrans NCR 22 between Petersfield and the Hangers"],"placesToEat":[{"name":"The Harrow Inn","type":"Traditional pub","notes":"16th-century Grade II listed, cask ale from the barrel, ploughman''s and home-cooked lunches, cash only, no Wi-Fi","url":"https://www.theharrowinnsteep.co.uk/"},{"name":"The Cricketers Inn","type":"Pub with rooms","notes":"Country pub in the village, dining and rooms","url":"https://www.thecricketerssteep.co.uk/"}],"pros":["Petersfield station only 1.6 miles — close enough to walk/cycle for the direct London Waterloo train","Steep CofE Primary Good (2024) with Outstanding behaviour and early years","Bedales School on the doorstep for the independent route","Inside the South Downs National Park, with the Ashford Hangers reserve and Hangers Way walking at the back door","Strong cultural fabric: literary heritage, Arts and Crafts architecture, active village hall"],"cons":["Property pricing reflects the postcode, the Bedales effect and the SDNP setting — entry level is meaningfully above the wider Petersfield average","Stock is dominated by period or larger houses; very limited starter / smaller-cottage supply","Strict planning regime (SDNP, conservation area, multiple listed buildings)","Some lanes are narrow with poor pavements; rural visibility on the A272 approach is challenging","Bedales drop-off and pick-up traffic loads the village lanes at term-time peaks"],"whoItSuits":"Buyers committed to Bedales for the independent route, or to Steep CofE Primary plus The Petersfield School / Churcher''s, who also want the walking-distance link to the main-line station. Also strong for cultural-and-creative households drawn by the Edward Thomas / Edward Barnsley / Bedales-Arts ecosystem, and for those who can absorb the SDNP planning regime in return for the landscape. Less suited to first-time buyers seeking lower entry pricing — for that, Sheet, Liss or Bordon are better-value alternatives in the same commuter belt.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":"Petersfield (1.6 mi)","primarySupermarket":"Waitrose Petersfield, Lavant Street (~2 mi)","images":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — Steep, Hampshire","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steep,_Hampshire"},{"label":"Wikipedia — Bedales School","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bedales_School"},{"label":"Wikipedia — The Harrow, Steep","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Harrow,_Steep"},{"label":"Ofsted — Steep CofE VC Primary","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/116319"},{"label":"The Harrow Inn","url":"https://www.theharrowinnsteep.co.uk/about.html"},{"label":"Edward Thomas in Steep (Slow Travel UK)","url":"https://www.slow-travel.uk/post/finding-the-poetry-of-edward-thomas-in-the-hampshire-village-of-steep"},{"label":"South Western Railway — Petersfield to London Waterloo","url":"https://www.southwesternrailway.com/train-times/petersfield-to-london-waterloo"},{"label":"East Hants DC — Council Tax 2026/27 (Steep parish)","url":"https://www.easthants.gov.uk/sites/default/files/2026-03/Council%20tax%20per%20valuation%20band%202026-27.pdf"}]},{"id":"steep-marsh-gu32","name":"Steep Marsh","village":"Steep Marsh","town":"Petersfield","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"GU32","hubCity":"Guildford","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Petersfield","coords":{"lat":50.9928,"lng":-0.93576},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"A small dispersed village in the civil parish of Steep, East Hampshire district, set in the South Downs National Park about two miles north of Petersfield. Steep Marsh is the marshy lower-lying ground east of Steep village proper, drained by the Ashford Stream and reached by a network of narrow lanes off the A272. The settlement is not a single nucleus: it is a string of period cottages, farmhouses and converted barns including Steep Marsh Farm Cottages, Brickyard Cottages and the cluster at Nine Acres. Day-to-day services are at Steep village (CofE primary, The Harrow Inn, Bedales School, All Saints Church) or in Petersfield itself, which is in walking range at 1.3–1.6 miles. The village historically had a condensed-milk factory and watercress beds drawing on the Ashford Stream; today it is overwhelmingly residential and agricultural.","character":"Dispersed marshland-edge settlement with period cottages and converted farm buildings; mature gardens, lots of trees, no central village green. Working countryside rather than chocolate-box; planning protections via both SDNP and the Steep Conservation Area apply.","amenities":["Steep Marsh Farm Cottages and Brickyard Cottages","Ashford Stream watercourse and footpaths","(at Steep village ~0.7 mi:) The Harrow Inn","The Cricketers Inn (Steep)","Steep CofE VC Primary School","All Saints Church, Steep (12th century)","Edward Barnsley Workshop"],"schools":[{"name":"Steep Church of England Voluntary Controlled Primary School","phase":"Primary","ofsted":"Good quality of education; Outstanding behaviour and early years (Oct 2024)","distance":"0.7–0.9 mi","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/116319"},{"name":"Bedales School","phase":"Independent (3–18, boarding and day)","ofsted":null,"distance":"0.8 mi","url":"https://www.bedales.org.uk/"},{"name":"Churcher''s College","phase":"Independent (3–18)","ofsted":null,"distance":"1.2 mi","url":"https://www.churcherscollege.com/"},{"name":"The Petersfield School","phase":"Secondary","ofsted":"Good","distance":"2.3 mi","url":"https://www.tps.hants.sch.uk/"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"London Waterloo","time":"1h 2m – 1h 17m direct","mode":"drive/cycle to Petersfield + direct South Western Railway","source":"https://www.southwesternrailway.com/train-times/petersfield-to-london-waterloo"},{"to":"Portsmouth Harbour","time":"~30m","mode":"Petersfield + direct South Western Railway","source":"https://www.southwesternrailway.com/travelling-with-us/at-the-station/petersfield"}],"nearestStation":"Petersfield (1.3 mi)","roads":"A272 (Petersfield–Winchester) at the south of the parish; A3 (London–Portsmouth) ~2 mi east at Petersfield"},"prices":{"avgSold12Mo":null,"avgDetached":null,"avgSemi":null,"avgTerraced":null,"avgFlat":null,"source":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/gu32-2bp.html","asOf":"2026-05"},"thingsToDo":["Hangers Way walking onto Shoulder of Mutton Hill","Ashford Hangers National Nature Reserve","Edward Thomas Poet''s Stone walk","Petersfield Heath (lake, model boats, Petersfield Museum)","Cycling on the lanes between Steep, Steep Marsh and Sheet"],"placesToEat":[{"name":"The Harrow Inn","type":"Traditional pub","notes":"16th-century Grade II listed; cask ale from the barrel; ploughman''s only; cash, no Wi-Fi","url":"https://www.theharrowinnsteep.co.uk/"},{"name":"The Cricketers Inn","type":"Country pub with rooms","notes":"Pub in Steep village, dining and accommodation","url":"https://www.thecricketerssteep.co.uk/"}],"pros":["Petersfield station only 1.3 miles — among the easier hamlet-to-mainline distances in the GU32 area","Inside the South Downs National Park","Catchment Steep CofE Primary rated Good with Outstanding behaviour (Oct 2024)","Strong independent-school cluster on the doorstep (Bedales, Churcher''s)","Ashford Hangers and Hangers Way for walking direct from the door"],"cons":["No shop, school or pub within the Steep Marsh boundary itself","Some lanes are subject to flooding from the Ashford Stream after heavy rain","Older stock often on oil heating and private drainage","Strict SDNP planning regime + Steep Conservation Area constrain alterations","Open-market turnover is thin: low single-digit annual sales per postcode unit"],"whoItSuits":"Households wanting period or barn-conversion stock in the South Downs with walking distance to Petersfield station, and willing to absorb the practicalities of marshland-edge property (drainage, occasional flooding, septic systems). Strong overlap with Bedales families. Less suited to first-time buyers — entry pricing here sits with Steep proper rather than with the wider Petersfield average.","broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":"Petersfield (1.3 mi)","primarySupermarket":"Waitrose Petersfield, Lavant Street (~1.8 mi)","images":[],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — Steep Marsh","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steep_Marsh"},{"label":"Wikipedia — Steep, Hampshire","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Steep,_Hampshire"},{"label":"Ofsted — Steep CofE VC Primary","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/116319"},{"label":"The Harrow Inn","url":"https://www.theharrowinnsteep.co.uk/about.html"},{"label":"South Western Railway — Petersfield to London Waterloo","url":"https://www.southwesternrailway.com/train-times/petersfield-to-london-waterloo"},{"label":"East Hants DC — Council Tax 2026/27 (Steep parish)","url":"https://www.easthants.gov.uk/sites/default/files/2026-03/Council%20tax%20per%20valuation%20band%202026-27.pdf"}]},{"id":"steeple-langford-sp4","name":"Steeple Langford","village":"Steeple Langford","town":"Salisbury","county":"Wiltshire","postcode":"SP4","hubCity":"Salisbury","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Salisbury","coords":{"lat":51.16316,"lng":-1.78372},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"stockbridge-so20","name":"Stockbridge","village":"Stockbridge","town":"Winchester","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO20","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Winchester","coords":{"lat":51.12808,"lng":-1.50172},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"researched","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"A handsome single-street town midway between Andover and Romsey, set in the Test Valley. Its wide High Street — a legacy of the drovers'' route from Wales — is now lined with tea rooms, gastropubs and independent specialist shops, with a deliberate scarcity of chain stores.","character":"Genteel, free-thinking, well-heeled rural; chalk-stream country with a strong fly-fishing identity (Houghton Fishing Club is the oldest in England, based at the Grosvenor Hotel).","amenities":["Independent High Street shops","Tea rooms, pubs and restaurants","Orvis flagship fly-fishing store","Robjent''s shooting/fishing outfitter","Single supermarket","Doctor''s surgery","Stockbridge Primary"],"schools":[{"name":"Stockbridge Primary School","phase":"Primary","type":"State","ofsted":"Good (2023)","distance":"In town","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/116028"},{"name":"Test Valley School","phase":"Secondary","type":"State","ofsted":"Good (2023)","distance":"~0.8 miles","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/23/116430"}],"transport":{"commutes":[{"to":"Winchester","mode":"Drive","typical":"~25 min","notes":"A30 eastbound"},{"to":"Southampton","mode":"Drive","typical":"~30–40 min","notes":"A3057/M27"},{"to":"London Waterloo","mode":"Train (from Winchester or Andover)","typical":"~1h + 20–30 min drive to station","notes":"No station in Stockbridge"}]},"prices":{"summary":"Stockbridge commands a premium over wider SO20 because of its high-street offer and Test Valley setting.","average":"£557,054","detached":"£808,571","semiDetached":"£426,364","terraced":"£345,769","flat":"£152,000","asOf":"2026-04","sourceUrl":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/SO20.html"},"thingsToDo":["Fly-fishing on the upper River Test","Walking the Test Way","Houghton Down / Danebury Hill Fort"],"placesToEat":["The Greyhound on the Test","The Three Cups Inn","The Grosvenor Hotel"],"pros":["Chalk-stream walks on the doorstep","Strong independent retail","Equidistant Andover ↔ Romsey ↔ Winchester"],"cons":["No railway station (nearest: Andover or Winchester)","Premium prices — a destination town, not a commuter dorm","A30 traffic through the High Street at peak times"],"whoItSuits":["Anglers and slow-food households","Buyers prioritising market-town amenities over commuter speed"],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[{"label":"Visit Hampshire — Stockbridge","url":"https://www.visit-hampshire.co.uk/explore/stockbridge-p524261"},{"label":"Orvis UK — Stockbridge store","url":"https://www.orvis.co.uk/pages/stockbridge-store"},{"label":"Robjent''s","url":"http://www.robjents.co.uk/"},{"label":"Ofsted — Stockbridge Primary School","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/21/116028"},{"label":"Ofsted — Test Valley School","url":"https://reports.ofsted.gov.uk/provider/23/116430"},{"label":"Rightmove House Prices SO20","url":"https://www.rightmove.co.uk/house-prices/SO20.html"},{"label":"Google Maps — Stockbridge to Winchester","url":"https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Stockbridge,+Hampshire/Winchester"}]},{"id":"stoford-sp2","name":"Stoford","village":"Stoford","town":"Salisbury","county":"Wiltshire","postcode":"SP2","hubCity":"Salisbury","regionDir":"","settlementType":"","subRegion":"Salisbury","coords":{"lat":51.04384,"lng":-1.84336},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]},{"id":"stoke-charity-so21","name":"Stoke Charity","village":"Stoke Charity","town":"Winchester","county":"Hampshire","postcode":"SO21","hubCity":"Southampton","regionDir":"North","settlementType":"Non-City","subRegion":"Winchester","coords":{"lat":51.05832,"lng":-1.29844},"coordsSource":"postcode-outward-approx","houseTypeIds":[],"status":"directory","priceSummary":null,"councilTaxBand":null,"overview":"","character":"","amenities":[],"schools":[],"transport":{"commutes":[]},"prices":{},"thingsToDo":[],"placesToEat":[],"pros":[],"cons":[],"whoItSuits":[],"broadbandMedianMbps":null,"nearestStation":null,"primarySupermarket":null,"images":[],"sources":[]}]'::jsonb) AS value;

